<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,901,927]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[353,539,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<typeStatus box="[353,456,901,927]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Holotype</typeStatus>
female
</emphasis>
(UF 15685) length 
<quantity box="[766,870,901,928]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.97" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="1.97">1.97 mm</quantity>
; head length 
<quantity box="[1021,1126,901,928]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.699999999999999" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="0.57">0.57 mm</quantity>
; head width 
<quantity box="[1271,1361,901,928]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
; pleon length 
<quantity box="[228,331,937,964]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="0.86">0.86 mm</quantity>
. Body extremely asymmetrical, 45°dextral distortion; no pigmentation (
<figureCitation box="[1137,1228,937,964]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis box="[199,260,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Head</emphasis>
oval, anterior margin deeply bilobate anteriorly, posterior margin rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1121,1213,973,1000]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1234,1287,974,999]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Eyes</emphasis>
absent. Both 
<emphasis box="[151,275,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">antennulae</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[330,433,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">antennae</emphasis>
rudimentary, with one article, without setae (
<figureCitation box="[942,1031,1009,1036]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1051,1143,1009,1035]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Barbula</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1158,1246,1009,1036]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
) with three slender falcate pointed lateral projections on each side. 
<emphasis box="[730,851,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Maxilliped</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[867,952,1045,1072]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
) with two segments, anterior segment subtriangular and much larger than irregularly-shaped posterior one, without palp, plectron slender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis box="[199,279,1118,1143]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Pereon</emphasis>
broadest across seventh pereomere (
<figureCitation box="[691,781,1117,1144]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Pereomeres 3–7 separated along middle region but fused along both sides. Coxal plates absent. Brood pouch enclosed by oostegites, open medially (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1247,1153,1180]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
). First oostegites highly asymmetrical; left one (
<figureCitation box="[494,608,1189,1216]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5F, G</figureCitation>
) with two subequal articles, internal ridge entire, with blunt posterolateral point; right one (
<figureCitation box="[346,460,1225,1252]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5H, I</figureCitation>
) with anterior article approximately three times longer than posterior article, internal ridge entire, with sharp posterolateral point. Seven 
<emphasis box="[731,847,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">pereopods</emphasis>
on right side of pereon, but only first pereopod discernible on left side. Pereopod with stout basis, small meri and carpi, short but pointed dactyli (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1300,1297,1324]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis box="[199,264,1333,1359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Pleon</emphasis>
of five pleomeres, extending away from pereomere 
<quantity box="[850,892,1333,1360]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1044,1134,1333,1360]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). First four pleomeres with uniramous, symmetrical lateral plates and four pairs of similar, uniramous pleopods. Terminal pleomere extending to form rounded pleotelson, terminating in sharp point (
<figureCitation box="[775,863,1405,1432]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3028150302" collectionCode="UF" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" specimenCode="UF 15685" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="paratype">
<emphasis box="[199,363,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<typeStatus box="[199,302,1442,1467]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Paratype</typeStatus>
male
</emphasis>
(
<specimenCode box="[378,494,1441,1468]" collectionCode="UF" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34858" name="Florida Museum of Natural History- Zoology, Paleontology and Paleobotany" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" type="Museum">UF 15685</specimenCode>
) length 
<quantity box="[587,690,1441,1468]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.06" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="1.06">1.06 mm</quantity>
; maximum width (across pereomere 5) 
<quantity box="[1135,1239,1441,1468]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="0.39">0.39 mm</quantity>
; head length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
; head width 
<quantity box="[340,442,1477,1504]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.20 mm</quantity>
, pleon length 
<quantity box="[600,703,1477,1504]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" unit="mm" value="0.31">0.31 mm</quantity>
. All pereomere regions distinct; pleon fused (
<figureCitation box="[1212,1333,1477,1504]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5K, L</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Head</emphasis>
elliptical, with rounded anterior margin, posterior margin fused with first pereomere; irregular dark eyes near posterolateral corners (
<figureCitation box="[465,556,1549,1576]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5K</figureCitation>
). Antennulae and antennae with three and five articles respectively, terminally setose; antennae prominently extending beyond head, visible in dorsal view. (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1146,1585,1612]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5L, M</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis box="[199,279,1622,1647]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Pereon</emphasis>
with seven segments (
<figureCitation box="[529,619,1621,1648]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5K</figureCitation>
). Pereomeres 3–5 subequal in width, lacking midventral projections, with patches of pigmentation on pereomeres 4–5 (
<figureCitation box="[653,743,1657,1684]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5K</figureCitation>
). Pereopods subequal, except last pair slightly larger than others (
<figureCitation box="[199,351,1693,1720]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5L, N, O</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis box="[199,264,1729,1755]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Pleon</emphasis>
fused into single piece (
<figureCitation box="[537,624,1729,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1235,1259]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,423,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-116@8.[151,1436,417,1211]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Hemiarthrus alphei n. sp., holotype female (UF 15685) (A–J), paratype male (UF 15685) (K–O): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; pl = pleopod; pt = pleotelson); B, ventral view; C, antennae; D, barbula, left side; E, left maxilliped, external view; F, left oostegite 1, external view; G, left oostegite 1, internal view; H, right oostegite 1, external view; I, right oostegite 1, internal view; J, right pereopod 2; K, dorsal view; L, ventral view; M, right antennula and antenna; N, left pereopod 1; O, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A, B, D = 1 mm; E = 0.64 mm; F–I = 0.8 mm; C, J–L = 0.28 mm; M, N, O = 0.12 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406611" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406611/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Fig. 5L</figureCitation>
), inflated, with scattered black pigmentation on dorsal surface. Pleopods and uropods absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1016,1801,1828]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" box="[199,1016,1801,1828]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1801,1827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name, 
<emphasis box="[560,637,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<taxonomicName authorityName="An &amp; Chen &amp; Paulay" authorityYear="2020" box="[560,633,1801,1827]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alphei">alphei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
refers to the host genus, 
<emphasis box="[918,1016,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<taxonomicName box="[918,1012,1801,1827]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Alpheus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="272" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,757,2008]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,250]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1837,1863]" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" authorityYear="1887" box="[657,800,1837,1863]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[657,800,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Hemiarthrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because the female has 5 pleomeres, four pairs of uniramous lateral plates and uniramous pleopods, and only one pereopod on the long side. It can be distinguished from the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" authorityYear="1887" box="[380,523,1909,1935]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[380,523,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">Hemiarthrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the barbula of the female having three pairs of falcate pointed lateral projections, pleomeres having well-developed, symmetrical lateral plates, and the pleon ending in a sharp point. The present species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pearse" baseAuthorityYear="1950" box="[527,668,1981,2007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="synalphei">
<emphasis box="[527,668,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">H. synalphei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pearse" baseAuthorityYear="1950" box="[1044,1185,1981,2007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="synalphei">
<emphasis box="[1044,1185,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">H. synalphei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(character states in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pearse" baseAuthorityYear="1950" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="271" order="Isopoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="270" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="synalphei">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="271" pageId="6" pageNumber="270">H. synalphei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given in parentheses) because the barbula of the female has three pairs of lateral projections (only two pairs); the pleotelson is short and oval (long and cylindrical); and the head of the male is fused with pereomere 1 (head separated from pereomere 1); it lacks sucker discs on the oostegite (with sucker discs on the oostegite).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406609" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4406609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406609/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="271" startId="7.[151,250,1924,1948]" targetBox="[151,1435,273,1901]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1924,1984]" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1924,1948]" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[279,443,1924,1948]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Alpheus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crinitus">
<emphasis box="[279,443,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">Alpheus crinitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(species complex) (UF 15684), with type of 
<taxonomicName authority="An &amp; Chen &amp; Paulay, 2020" authorityName="An &amp; Chen &amp; Paulay" authorityYear="2020" box="[891,1088,1924,1948]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alphei" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[891,1088,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">Hemiarthrus alphei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1094,1150,1924,1948]" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1094,1150,1924,1948]" pageId="7" pageNumber="271" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(UF 15685) attached; image of live specimens; host and parasite (A, B), parasite (C, D).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis box="[199,602,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boyko &amp; Williams" authorityYear="2004" box="[199,448,151,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="surculus">Hemiarthrus surculus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pearse" baseAuthorityYear="1950" box="[460,602,151,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="synalphei">H. synalphei</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="An &amp; Chen &amp; Paulay" authorityYear="2020" box="[659,765,151,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alphei">
<emphasis box="[659,765,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">H. alphei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
infest alpheid shrimp, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kroyer" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1027,1201,151,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[1027,1201,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">H. abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
infests pandalid and hippolytid shrimp, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1914" box="[432,626,187,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nematocarcini">
<emphasis box="[432,626,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">H. nematocarcini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is parasitic on nematocarcinid shrimp. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chopra, B." box="[1062,1225,187,213]" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" pagination="411 - 550" refId="ref9204" refString="Chopra, B. (1923) Bopyrid isopods parasitic on Indian Macrura. Records of the Indian Museum, 25 (5), 411 - 550." type="journal article" year="1923">Chopra (1923)</bibRefCitation>
thought 
<taxonomicName box="[1323,1437,187,213]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Palaemon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1323,1437,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">Palaemon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens parasitized by bopyrids are difficult to identify owing to the fact that the parasite inhibits sexual activity and prevents the full manifestation of secondary sexual characters, and females never carry eggs. Rajkumar 
<emphasis box="[1373,1422,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">et al</emphasis>
., (2011) found that infestation with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nobili" authorityYear="1906" box="[543,758,295,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Epipenaeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingens">
<emphasis box="[543,758,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">Epipenaeon ingens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had a significant effect on reproduction in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alcock" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Metapenaeopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stridulans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">Metapenaeopsis stridulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. But the host of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="An &amp; Chen &amp; Paulay" authorityYear="2020" box="[461,567,331,357]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Hemiarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="272" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alphei">
<emphasis box="[461,567,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="272">H. alphei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was ovigerous, suggesting that hosts can remain reproductive after bopyrid infestation.
</paragraph>
